1. get start with heysasha_v2.yml
 $ docker-compose -f heysasha_v3.yml up  
 - check localhost:3000

2. add a table via a script
  - copy localfile.sql to postgreSQL 
   $ docker cp ./localfile.sql db:/file.sql
 
  - update table via postgreSQL in docker container
   $ docker exec -it db psql -U api -f file.sql

  - The status in localhost:3000 was changed

3. backup/restore database

4. runs a init.sql file when postgreSQL boot up 
